commit.message:
Fix build with newer meson versions

Fix the following meson error:
"i18n.merge_file does not take any positional arguments."
meson: require meson 0.50 for / support
doc: update author list
build: port to meson
doc: README update

gtk-v4l-device: Add support for v4l-subdevs

Modern v4l2 devices may have subdevs which have their own controls,
add support for these.

Also skip (sub)devs without any controls so as to not needlessly
clutter the device-list.

Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>

Update ICON_LOC

Update ICON_LOC to fix the window-icon not being found on systems
which don't have the old GNOME icon-theme installed.

gtk-v4l-device: remove source on finalize

This fixes us from getting events from it, with a user_data argument
pointing to the finalized object, when the fd gets re-used if another device
gets plugged in later, and that device then generates ctrl events.
